A Bombus ternarius is a species of bumblebee native to North America. 
It is characterized by its bright yellow coloration on its thorax and abdomen, with black stripes. 
They have fuzzy hair covering their body, commonly known as "fur." 
Their wings are clear and translucent. 
This species can be found throughout the northeastern region of the United States and into Canada. 
They are known to be important pollinators of flowering plants. 
Their colonies consist of a queen and female worker bees.
